caption: The atmosphere is great here! I like the more casual vibe, you could come for a more fancy brunch experience or for a more casual snack. The Purple Haze was SO good, it's definitely a must try. The bagel sandwich was delicious, the chive cream cheese was amazing. The berry crepes were also great, the granola on top of the crepes is such a fun addition. I will definitely come here again!

Food was excellent, came out quick, good value and portion size. 4 stars only because service could've been better, we had to ask for water a few times but only one glass was ever brought, other tables had their own carafe of water, and we had to ask for cutlery. Felt like we were forgotten about honestly.
Weird menu, super good, but pricey!

Wake 'n Bacon lives up to the hype. I for one had never heard of the place before, until my partner and I decided to find a new breakfast place around town. Let me tell you, hands down some of the best food/breakfast you'll find in Chicago. Their chicken and waffles are to die for as well. If you're on the fence about this place, trust me it's more than worth it to try out and enjoy the wonderful foods and atmosphere.

Loved the food! The Chicken ‘n Waffles, Berry Crepes, the Phatty, the Purple Haze....all amazing. The ordering process via QR code was efficient. My only critique is the lack of staff interaction. Would have been nice to get a glass of water especially since I tipped 25% and the only time we spoke with a staff member is when he dropped off our plates.  It’s the personal touch that makes a difference. But if you’re looking for a great meal and fun decor, check it out!

The staff here are always very helpful and friendly when I’ve come in. They do their best to accommodate.  The food is always so tasty as well. The tator tots that come with most of the meals are always so crispy and crunchy. I normally order the baegal with spam and it’s dynamite. The chicken and waffle is good as well and so is their burger. Definitely a cute spot and love the flowers in the ceiling.  Drinks are also very tasty and I love their purple haze ( Coffee with ube). Also, I enjoy that you can add CBD to most items which is a treat especially since I work from home and sometimes need something to soothe the soul during these long meetings.
A must!!!

Overall it was a good experience there. It was easy to find street parking. I love how you can order by scanning a QR code. The food was a little heavy for me. Good vibe. Decent service. You can take picture at the front. If I lived near here I would go there often.

Leaving a review here, on Facebook, on Yelp, and anywhere else I can think of because EVERYONE needs to try this place! It's the PERFECT spot for a celebration, a chill afternoon, or a fun date! Menu is eccentric but comfortable, affordable but not cheap, and the drinks are PHENOMENAL. Everything is so gorgeous you'll be hard pressed not to snap a few photos, and they even have a cute photo booth. Bring your friends, bring your family, because I 10/10 recommend spending at least one afternoon enjoying the wonder that is Wake N Bacon!

Delicious food. I tried the Chicken and Waffles and the Philly. Both were very good. Also was super excited to find a place with Salvadorian Quesadilla. I would also make sure to pick up the "breakup" brownie.  I just wished they had more warm tea options.
It seems like this place is more focused on the instagram photos than the food.
Small and trendy. Waffle and chicken was yummy.

I loved the place! The food is delicious and the coffee was great but I guess I was expecting something more restaurant like as opposed as a cafe but that was on me. At the end it is a solid 3 star place 😃
Horrible   overpriced and huge attempts at being sheik
Great food, beautiful interior!

This place is beautiful. The food is amazing and the staff is fantastic! The menu has the perfect variety of delicious food choices and a great drink menu. The restaurant is clean and just wonderful, even the bathroom is unique. Highly recommended, I will definitely be back as often as possible!

Tried the Adobo Philly Wrap and loved it. It's a chicken cheeseteak-style of sandwich with au jus on the side plus some tater tots. The restaurant has a pretty cool looking vibe inside. I'm excited to try some of the creative breakfast options!

UBE coffee 🤤 I think about this coffee constantly. It was so good I can’t wait to go back for another one.  Chicken and waffles was pretty good, different than the typical style. Chicken was delish, waffle was lacking but still overall good.  The chia pudding I got solely because of the fruity pebbles and I would do it again. The coconut jelly (green squares) were surprisingly my favorite part.
Freezing cold.
Loved this place so much. And the food was amazing!
The food was good and the liquid sunshine is amazing !

Wake ‘n Bacon has easily become my favorite coffee + brunch spot in Lakeview! The food is fantastic and has a creative mix of latin, asian & american flavors. My favorites so far are the breakfast tacos (tasty tortillas!), burrito & ube pancake. I love how their eggs are seasoned and the delicious thick-cut bacon. The purple haze latte is also really well done.  It’s easy to see that the owners, Sarah & Gabe, truly care about their customers and go the extra mile to make all experiences a welcomed one. Jason & Mandyn are always so friendly and make some delicious drinks too! I’ve really enjoyed some of the unique offerings like getting to test out new menu items in their Egghead Club, coffee subscriptions, & the bonus face masks in to-go orders. Thanks Wake ‘n Bake!

I am not the biggest fan of breakfast burritos but I give this a try and wow it was great! First off it was as big if not bigger than the size of a chipotle burrito, the egg was fresh , rice and beans sardine and a surprise of tots in it! That tots on the side are very good as well (salty in a good way) . The bagel was very good too and chive cream cheese tasted homemade:) overall great price and great food/portion will be back!  Also if you order out they give you a free mask and a code for a free drink
My coffee was purple.  My pancakes were purple.  Very clean floors.
Delicious Food, Great Ambience and friendly staff.

THE BEST CHICAGO BREAKFAST I HAVE EVER HAD! As someone who doesn’t love to cook, ordering out is my favorite way to spend money. Out of all of the breakfast food I’ve treated myself to while living in Chicago, this is BY FAR the best I’ve ever had! I highly recommend checking it out - you will NOT regret it!

I've ordered from Wake'n'Bacon three times now and each time was a treat. They have a super unique menu and even the "standard" items have a creative twist, which I really appreciate. The staff could not be more friendly and I can easily see myself becoming a regular here once dining restrictions are lifted. The only major downside for me is that Wake'n'Bacon doesn't have a nutritional menu, so the health-conscious will have a lot of guesswork when it comes to tracking their calories and macros.

Can’t go wrong with anything on the menu, everything is so unique. The Phatty, #Baegoal, Veggie Stir Fry, Breakup Brownies, Quesadillas, and the Halo Halo Chia Chia are all delicious. The HHCC pudding is so fun and healthy. The fruity pebbles are such a good addition! Love this place.
The food here is great and the space is so beautiful. I can't wait till we can eat inside again so I can do bunch here every weekend!

Chicken and waffles are fantastic as everyone has already mentioned but the big surprise was the halo halo chia chia.  Very different from anything I have ever tasted before.   My 9 year old daughter said we have to get 2 next time we go back!

Beautifully executed concept, this restaurant thought of everything, making it a fun spot to grab a quick coffee, a cocktail/beer with a small bite, or a full scale brunch. The food is deliberate in flavor and quality. Whether you’re picking up or dining in, the staff are friendly and accommodating, and the service is everything people desire from modern living and convenience. If you’re not lucky enough to live in the neighborhood for frequent visits, it’s worth seeking out for taste.
Super unique and amazing food, can't wait to go back. The mauoWOWie with tots was exactly what I needed.

Went to Wake 'n Bacon for the first time this weekend and will definitely be going back!! We got the ube pancakes and the chicken and waffles, along with the Fernando cocktail, and all were absolutely delicious.
Highly recommend chicken and waffles

The chia pudding should be renamed on the menu as: "MIRACLES EXIST". Do yourself a favor -- experience awe in the form of brunch. Your brain will hardly be able to reconcile the ingredients in your bowl with what can only be described as a supernatural flavor explosion. In fact, everything on the menu was this way for us. It all looks lovely, but to dine here is to see the light, you'll leave singing their praises for sure.

Supper delicious!  Got the peach crepe, chicken and waffles, burger, maui wowie, adobe dip and the chia chia for take out.  The Adobe dip and Maui Wowie were amazing and have unique flavors that you wouldn't get anywhere else.  Everything was amazing and plan to order what we didn't get from the menu next time (plus the adobe dip, maui wowie, and the chia chia again!).  Good as leftovers too!
This place was amazing! I has the chicken and waffles and it was a fantastic!!
Ordered the peach crepe, chicken and waffles, burger, maui wowie, adobe dip and the chia chia for take out and they were all so good!!! Ordered for pick up and it was still delicious

Fun ambiance with the floral ceiling, photo station, and dry erase wall for the kids to draw on. Coffee and lemonade are tasty. The burger was cooked perfectly with all the fixings. Tots are fun! Adobe dip has juicy chicken and is a unique take on a philly and Bahn mi fusion sandwich. Warning: the marinated peppers are spicy 🔥🔥 but tasty. Side bacon was perfectly griddled with a smoky maple glaze. Looking forward to coming back to try all the sweet breakfast items and cocktails, that looked delicious at other tables. Family-owned busines who have put a lot of time, thought, and effort into this new brunch spot.
The food is delicious! I will definitely be back...i recommend the ube pancakes!
